# Docker build-context exclusions (WS2.1/WS2.2 foundation images).
#
# The daemon/worker images build from the repo root context (`docker build .`).
# The multi-stage builders only need Go source + go.mod/sum + the Makefile, so we
# prune the large non-source trees to keep the context (and each layer) small.
# NOTE: `.git` is excluded — the Makefile's COMMIT_HASH is passed as a build-arg
# (see Dockerfile.daemon), so no .git is needed inside the build. Excluding it
# keeps the context lean.
.git
.claude/worktrees
.kerf
.memory
plans
testdata
docs
specs
node_modules
*.log
.tools
twins
